<h2>Why Do Blank Pages Appear in PDFs?</h2>

<p>Common causes of blank pages in PDFs:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Merging PDFs:</strong> When combining PDFs with different page counts, separator or filler pages may be inserted</li>
  <li><strong>Word processor exports:</strong> Microsoft Word and Google Docs sometimes insert a blank page at the end to round out to an even page count</li>
  <li><strong>Scanner errors:</strong> Double-sided scanners sometimes scan a blank reverse side of a one-sided document</li>
  <li><strong>Section breaks:</strong> Documents with section breaks force content to start on a new page, leaving the previous page partially or fully empty</li>
  <li><strong>Print-ready layouts:</strong> Some formats require even page counts for booklet printing, leaving the last page blank</li>
</ul>

<h2>How to Remove Blank Pages in Microsoft Word (Before Exporting as PDF)</h2>

<p>If you have access to the source Word document, it is easier to fix blank pages there before exporting:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Press <strong>Ctrl+End</strong> to go to the end of the document.</li>
  <li>If you see a blank page, click in it and press <strong>Backspace</strong> until it disappears.</li>
  <li>To reveal hidden section breaks: Home tab → Show/Hide (¶) button → delete any unwanted section breaks.</li>
  <li>Export to PDF again: File → Save As → PDF.</li>
</ol>

<h2>How to Remove Blank Pages in Adobe Acrobat</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Open the PDF in Adobe Acrobat (paid).</li>
  <li>Click the <strong>Page Thumbnails</strong> panel on the left.</li>
  <li>Scroll through thumbnails to identify blank pages.</li>
  <li>Click a blank page thumbnail to select it (Ctrl+click for multiple).</li>
  <li>Right-click → <strong>Delete Pages…</strong> → confirm.</li>
</ol>

<p>This method is precise but requires Acrobat and manual identification of each blank page — the automated browser tool above is faster for documents with many blanks.</p>

<h2>How to Remove Blank Pages on Mac (Preview)</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Open the PDF in Preview.</li>
  <li>Go to <strong>View → Thumbnails</strong> to show the sidebar.</li>
  <li>Click each blank page thumbnail you want to remove.</li>
  <li>Press <strong>Delete</strong> (or Edit → Delete).</li>
  <li>Save the file: File → Export as PDF.</li>
</ol>

<h2>Tips for Best Results</h2>

<ul>
  <li>If the tool removes too many pages (e.g. pages with only headers), lower the threshold slider</li>
  <li>If blank pages remain, raise the threshold — some "blank" pages may have a few invisible characters or whitespace</li>
  <li>For scanned PDFs, run OCR first to add a text layer before using this tool</li>
  <li>Always check the page count before and after to verify the expected number of pages were removed</li>
</ul>

